# Building Supply Store API

## Brick Type [/bricks/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: XYZ42 - ID of a brick type.
+ Attributes
    + id
    + name (string, required)
    + colors: red, brown (array)
    + dimensions (array)
        + 20, 30, 40 (array[number])

### Get Particular Brick Type [GET]

Attributes defined in resource are referenced from payload.

+ Request (application/json)
+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)
    + Attributes (Brick Type)

## Available Brick Types [/bricks]

### Create a New Brick Type [POST]

Attributes defined in resource are referenced from action.

+ Attributes (Brick Type)
+ Request (application/json)
+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)
    + Attributes (Brick Type)

## Customers [/customers]

### Get All Customers [GET]

Attributes defined as data structure are referenced from payload.

+ Request (application/json)
+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)
    + Attributes (array[User])

### Add New Customer [POST]

Attributes defined as data structure are referenced from action.

+ Attributes (User)
+ Request (application/json)
+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)
    + Attributes (User)

## Data Structures

### User (object)

+ id
+ name (string)
+ shoeSize: 42 (number)
+ address
    + street
    + city (string, nullable)
